title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 69th Street

text:
Central Park West, west side, from 69th to 71st Streets. At the left on the N.W. corner of 69th Street is the clearing resulting from the demolition of two buildings. The white building with Corinthian columns in the centre is the Portuguese synagogue Congregation Shearith Israel.

October 20, 1928.

P. L. Sperr, Photographer.
